					Latest Key Developments (Source: Significant Developments)




Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd decides to pay FY 2015 dividend of EUR 0.025/share
Wednesday, 29 Jun 2016 09:21am EDT 
Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd : Says decides to pay dividend equal to 7.5 pct of the nominal share value, 0.025 euros per share .Sets record day to be July 8 and payment date on August 4. 
			
Full Article





Petrolina Holdings issues earnings guidance for H1 FY 2016
Monday, 27 Jun 2016 11:06am EDT 
Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd : Reported on Friday that announces that profits for H1 FY 2016 are expected to be increased compared to H1 FY 2015 .The increase in profits compared to the corresponding period of last year is mainly due to the more efficient management of the gross profit margin, partly offset by increased sales and distribution expenses. 
			
Full Article





Petrolina Holdings: Creation of consortium
Wednesday, 22 Jun 2016 09:57am EDT 
Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd : Reported on Tuesday that enters into a shareholders’ agreement with Hellenic Petroleum Cyprus Ltd, Intergaz Ltd and Synergas Ltd for the creation of a consortium in the form of a limited liability company under the proposed name Vassiliko LPG Plant Ltd (VLP) . The aim of VLP is to construct a liquid gas terminal on land granted for this purpose by the Government to the shareholders of the consortium within the Vassilikos Industrial . and Energy Area . The capital expenditure required for the construction of the project is estimated at approximately 23 million euros ($25.99 million) and will be financed via a combination of own funds of the shareholders and a bank loan . The time required for the construction of the terminal is estimated at 24 months from the date of obtaining all required permits .Under the shareholders’ agreement, PHL will own 35% of the share capital of VLP, while management will be exercised on a equal basis by its four shareholders. 
			
Full Article





Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd:Change in shareholding
Wednesday, 11 May 2016 06:51am EDT 
Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd : Zigron Holdings Limited, Bestwick Securities INC, Global Systems Limited and Grevil Assets LTD SA sell 3.1 million common shares of Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd for 2.8 million euros ($3.19 million) to TOMA (OFFSHORE) S.A.L. .BNP PARIBAS sells 3.1 million common shares of Petrolina Holdings Public Ltd for 2.8 million euros to Zigron Holdings Limited, Bestwick Securities INC, Global Systems Limited and Grevil Assets LTD SA. 
			
